  "text": "The parameters h T are the so-called bandwidths. Under fairly mild regularity conditions, the conditional method of moments is consistent and yields asymptotically normally distributed estimates. See [CITATION_1] for specifics. The estimator is less complicated than it looks. The conditional method of moments estimates of ␣( z, ⌬t, ) and c( z, ⌬t, ) are the ␣ and c that set to zero the -weighted sample average of m i,tϩ⌬t . The role of the weights and of the bandwidths h T is to emphasize observations with z i,t similar to z, relative to observations with z i,t different from z.",
